ion rootpage-Falchion skin-vector action-view\">\t\t<div id=\"mw-page-base\" class=\"noprint\"></div>\n\t\t<div id=\"mw-head-base\" class=\"noprint\"></div>\n\t\t<div id=\"content\" class=\"mw-body\" role=\"main\">\n\t\t\t<a id=\"top\"></a>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"mw-indicators mw-body-content\">\n</div>\n<h1 id=\"firstHeading\" class=\"firstHeading\" lang=\"en\">Falchion</h1>\t\t\t<div id=\"bodyContent\" class=\"mw-body-content\">\n\t\t\t\t<div id=\"siteSub\" class=\"noprint\">From NetHackWiki</div>\t\t\t\t<div id=\"contentSub\"></div>\n\t\t\t\t<div id=\"jump-to-nav\"></div>\t\t\t\t<a class=\"mw-jump-link\" href=\"#mw-head\">Jump to navigation</a>\n\t\t\t\t<a class=\"mw-jump-link\" href=\"#p-search\">Jump to search</a>\n\t\t\t\t<div id=\"mw-content-text\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\" class=\"mw-content-ltr\"><div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\">\n<table class=\"prettytable\" style=\"margin: 0;\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th colspan=\"2\"><span class=\"nhsym clr-cyan\">)</span> <a href=\"/index.php?title=Special:Upload&amp;wpDestFile=Falchion.png\" class=\"new\" title=\"File:Falchion.png\">File:Falchion.png</a>\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Name\n</th>\n<td>falchion\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Appearance\n</th>\n<td>falchion\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Damage vs. small\n</th>\n<td>1d12\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Damage vs. large\n</th>\n<td>1d16\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>To-hit bonus\n</th>\n<td>+1\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Weapon skill\n</th>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Scimitar\" title=\"Scimitar\">scimitar</a>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Size\n</th>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/One-handed\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"One-handed\">one-handed</a>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Base price\n</th>\n<td>10 <a href=\"/wiki/Zorkmid\" title=\"Zorkmid\">zm</a><br />(+10/positive <br />enchant)\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Weight\n</th>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Weight\" title=\"Weight\">30</a>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Material\n</th>\n<td><a href=\"/wiki/Iron\" title=\"Iron\">iron</a>\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n</div>\n<p>A <b>falchion</b> is a type of two-handed <a href=\"/wiki/Weapon\" title=\"Weapon\">weapon</a> that appears in <i><a href=\"/wiki/SpliceHack\" title=\"SpliceHack\">SpliceHack</a></i> and  <i><a href=\"/wiki/Hack%27EM\" title=\"Hack&#39;EM\">Hack'EM</a></i>.\n</p><p>In SpliceHack, the falchion uses the scimitar skill. In Hack'EM it uses the saber skill which was merged with the scimitar skill.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Generation\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Generation</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Strategy\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Strategy</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Origin\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Origin</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Generation\">Generation</span></h2>\n<p>Falchions are uncommon, appearing slightly less than scimitars.\n</p><p>In both variants, <a href=\"/wiki/Barbarian\" title=\"Barbarian\">Barbarians</a> can start with falchion/scimitar combo as an alternative to the battle-axe/short sword weapon set.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Strategy\">Strategy</span></h2>\n<p>In Hack'EM it is possible to create one by #crafting two <a href=\"/wiki/Scimitar\" title=\"Scimitar\">scimitars</a> together. \n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span></h2>\n<p>The falchion first appears in <a href=\"/wiki/SpliceHack\" title=\"SpliceHack\">SpliceHack</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Origin\">Origin</span></h2>\n<div class=\"noprint sidebox\">\n<div style=\"float: left;\"><div class=\"floatnone\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Fair-use-wikipedia-logo.png\" class=\"image\" title=\"Wikipedia\"><img alt=\"Wikipedia\" src=\"/images/thumb/f/f8/Fair-use-wikipedia-logo.png/50px-Fair-use-wikipedia-logo.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"50\" srcset=\"/images/f/f8/Fair-use-wikipedia-logo.png 1.5x\" /></a></div></div>\n<div style=\"margin-left: 60px;\"><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Main_Page\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"wikipedia:Main Page\">Wikipedia</a> has an article about:\n<div style=\"margin-left: 10px;\"><i><b><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Falchion\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"wikipedia:Falchion\">Falchion</a></b></i></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>The term falchion refers to various designs of European swords, but generally describes single-edged one-handed blades, often with a slightly curved tip.  In appearance, they could vary from a <a href=\"/wiki/Scimitar\" title=\"Scimitar\">scimitar</a>-like weapon all the way to something resembling a meat cleaver.  Curiously, while falchions are frequently depicted in medieval European artwork, only a few dozen survive to the current day, compared to thousands of double-edged blades (e.g. <a href=\"/wiki/Long_sword\" title=\"Long sword\">long swords</a>).\n</p><p><br />\n</p>\n<div style=\"display:none; right:10px; padding-bottom: 17px\" class=\"metadata topicon nopopups\"><div style=\"margin-top: -10px\"><a href=\"/wiki/NetHackWiki:Next_version\" title=\"This article has been updated to reflect NetHack 3.6.6. Click here for more information.\"><img alt=\"This article has been updated to reflect NetHack 3.6.6. Click here for more information.\" src=\"/images/5/57/Nh366-icon.png\" width=\"32\" height=\"32\" /></a></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20240926183509\nCache expiry: 604800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time us